"callout_pointer"></div></div><p>For superior-quality cookware that will last a lifetime, we recommend getting the <a class="product-link" href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/17421/53965/4/59241/?merchant=Amazon" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer" target="_blank" data-gtm-trigger="product_link" data-store="Amazon" data-vars-store="Amazon" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/17421/53965/4/59241/?merchant=Amazon">All-Clad Stainless 10-Piece Set</a>. The pros we talked to said that All-Clad tri-ply cookware is the best for both professional and home use because it’s so durable. In our tests, the All-Clad pans heated evenly, were comfortable to hold, and tackled every cooking job without any hiccups. Though the largest skillet measures only 10 inches instead of 12, this set will outfit your kitchen with all the other pots and pans you’re ever likely to need. And if you’re partial to keeping your cookware bright and shiny, note that in our tests this set was one of the few that looked like new after cleaning.</p></section><div class="_17850657" data-scp="sbs_callout"><h3 id="everything-we-recommend" class="f3350a61">Everything we recommend</h3><div class="_2666695a" data-gtm-element="sbs_callouts"><div class="a7ed89b1 global-cob eefda761 cff8e815 _6facab4a" data-scp="callout"><h4 class="b1dfff67" data-scp="callout_label">Our pick</h4><div id="callout-intro-callouts-0-2" class="f4873f0f" data-gtm-element="callout" data-scp="callout_item"><div class="_32e239ce"><div class="_892e4e17"><div class="a35ae31e"><a href="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/36738/163977/4/111078?merchant=Wayfair" class="bac232ef product-merchant-link-button" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" data-store="Wayfair" data-vars-store="Wayfair" data-vars-outbound-link="https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/36738/163977/4/111078?merchant=Wayfair" data-gtm-trigger="callout_product_link_image" data-scp="callout_image"><figure class="_92ef929f global_