 chicken to baking cornbread.","type":"text"}]},{"data":"\n","type":"text"},{"type":"tag","name":"li","attribs":{},"children":[{"type":"tag","name":"strong","attribs":{},"children":[{"data":"Copper","type":"text"}]},{"data":" is an excellent conductor of heat, but it’s very expensive and difficult to maintain. However, we did test the ","type":"text"},{"type":"tag","name":"a","attribs":{"class":"product-link","href":"https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/24521/130679/4/74844/?merchant=Williams-Sonoma","rel":"nofollow noopener","target":"_blank","data-gtm-trigger":"product_link","data-store":"Williams-Sonoma","data-vars-store":"Williams-Sonoma","data-vars-outbound-link":"https://www.nytimes.com/wirecutter/out/link/24521/130679/4/74844/?merchant=Williams-Sonoma"},"children":[{"data":"All-Clad Copper Core 10-Piece Cookware Set","type":"text"}]},{"data":" because it has a stainless steel exterior.","type":"text"}]},{"data":"\n","type":"text"}]},{"data":"\n","type":"text"},{"type":"tag","name":"h3","attribs":{},"children":[{"data":"Features and accessories to avoid","type":"text"}]},{"data":"\n","type":"text"},{"type":"tag","name":"p","attribs":{},"children":[{"data":"We excluded sets with glass lids because they can break or crack easily if dropped. They also offer little advantage over stainless steel lids because you can’t see through them when they’re covered with condensation. Pot and pan lids should fit well but somewhat loosely, with just enough wiggle room to allow steam to escape.","type":"text"}]},{"data":"\n","type":"text"},{"type":"tag","name":"p","attribs":{},"children":[{"data":"We dismissed sets with plastic handles, because even those made to withstand high temperatures can deteriorate over time. Ideally, we wanted cookware that could safely withstand oven temperatures of at least 500 degrees Fahrenheit, which ruled out most plastic components. Several members of our staff have also seen plastic handles crack after spending time in the dishwasher.",